{
  "doc_id": "FC-LS",
  "source_pdf": "/Users/zwy/毕设/V7/data/raw/FC-LS.pdf",
  "page": 160,
  "spans": [
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0002",
      "text": " 141",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0003",
      "text": "6.3.2.5  Responses to N_Port Login - No Fabric present",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        357.03,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0004",
      "text": "The following are possible responses the Nx_Port may receive in response to transmitting a PLOGI",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        82.97,
        539.99,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0005",
      "text": "in a point-to-point configuration:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        94.97,
        236.0,
        106.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0006",
      "text": "a) LS_ACC reply Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the PLOGI, and the Common Ser-",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        118.97,
        540.1,
        130.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0007",
      "text": "vice N_Port/F_Port bit  = 0  (Nx_Port).  The D_ID of the LS_ACC shall be the S_ID from the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        130.97,
        539.92,
        142.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0008",
      "text": "PLOGI.  The S_ID shall be the destination Nx_Port's N_Port_ID assigned by the D_ID in the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        142.96,
        539.97,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0009",
      "text": "PLOGI.  The Payload shall include the Service Parameters for the destination Nx_Port, a 64-bit",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        154.96,
        540.03,
        166.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0010",
      "text": "N_Port_Name and a 64-bit Node_Name.  The N_Port Service Parameters are as specified in",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        166.96,
        539.95,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0011",
      "text": "6.6.  The applicability of the Service Parameters to N_Port Login are given in tables 150 and",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        178.96,
        539.73,
        190.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0012",
      "text": "155.  This is the normal response to a N_Port Login request.  The Nx_Port may begin normal",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        190.96,
        539.9,
        202.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0013",
      "text": "communication with the remote N_Port.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        202.96,
        297.37,
        214.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 8,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0014",
      "text": "b) P_BSY Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the PLOGI.  The D_ID shall be the S_ID",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        226.96,
        539.98,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0015",
      "text": "of the PLOGI.  The destination Nx_Port is busy.  The Nx_Port may retry the PLOGI again later.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        238.96,
        539.96,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0016",
      "text": "c)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        262.96,
        114.35,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0017",
      "text": "P_RJT Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the PLOGI.  The D_ID shall be the S_ID of",
      "bbox": [
        122.37,
        262.96,
        540.15,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0018",
      "text": "the PLOGI.  The reason code contained in the Payload determines the Nx_Port’s action.  If the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        274.96,
        540.05,
        286.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0019",
      "text": "reason code is \"Class not supported\", the Nx_Port may attempt N_Port Login in a different",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        286.96,
        539.98,
        298.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0020",
      "text": "Class.  For other reason codes, the Nx_Port should respond according to the code.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        298.96,
        489.6,
        310.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0021",
      "text": "d) LS_RJT Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the PLOGI.  The D_ID of the LS_ACC",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        322.96,
        539.99,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0022",
      "text": "shall be the N_Port_ID of the destination Nx_Port.  The reason code contained in the Payload",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        334.96,
        540.05,
        346.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0023",
      "text": "determines the Nx_Port’s action.  The Nx_Port may alter the Service Parameters based on the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        346.96,
        540.07,
        358.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0024",
      "text": "reason code and originate a new PLOGI.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        358.96,
        303.46,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0025",
      "text": "e) PLOGI Sequence.  The D_ID is the address identifier of receiving Nx_Port.  The S_ID is the",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        382.96,
        539.97,
        394.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0026",
      "text": "N_Port_ID of the originating Nx_Port.  The OX_ID is as assigned by the originating Nx_Port.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        394.96,
        540.02,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0027",
      "text": "The Payload shall include a 64-bit N_Port_Name and 64-bit Node_Name of the Nx_Port origi-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        406.96,
        539.97,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0028",
      "text": "nating the PLOGI.  This indicates a collision with N_Port Login from the destination Nx_Port.  If",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        418.96,
        540.05,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0029",
      "text": "the received N_Port_Name is less than the receiving Nx_Port's N_Port_Name, the Nx_Port",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        430.96,
        540.01,
        442.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0030",
      "text": "sends LS_RJT to the originating Nx_Port with reason code \"Command already in progress\".  If",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        442.96,
        540.16,
        454.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0031",
      "text": "the received N_Port_Name is greater than its N_Port_Name, the Nx_Port processes the re-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        454.96,
        540.07,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0032",
      "text": "ceived PLOGI.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        466.96,
        187.4,
        478.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 8,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0033",
      "text": "f)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        490.96,
        112.14,
        502.07
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0034",
      "text": "No Response may indicate a delivery error, e.g., error on the physical transport.  The Nx_Port",
      "bbox": [
        122.38,
        490.96,
        540.05,
        502.07
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0035",
      "text": "shall perform error recovery per FC-FS-2.  The Nx_Port may originate a new PLOGI after re-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        502.96,
        540.08,
        514.07
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0036",
      "text": "covery.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        514.96,
        154.57,
        526.07
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0037",
      "text": "g) If the received N_Port_Name is equal to its N_Port_Name, then the Nx_Port is connected to it-",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        538.96,
        539.95,
        550.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0038",
      "text": "self and this case is outside the scope of this standard.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        550.96,
        364.6,
        562.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0039",
      "text": "6.3.3",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        574.96,
        118.22,
        586.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0040",
      "text": "SOFs",
      "bbox": [
        128.22,
        574.96,
        154.28,
        586.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0041",
      "text": "N_Port Login is only supported in Class 1, 2, and 3.  Since the destination Nx_Port may not support",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        598.96,
        539.93,
        610.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0042",
      "text": "all these classes for Login, the PLOGI Sequence may require retransmission in a different Class with",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        610.96,
        539.73,
        622.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0043",
      "text": "the appropriate SOF in the same manner described for Fabric Login (see 6.2.3).  Login is valid for all",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        622.96,
        540.08,
        634.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p160_s0044",
      "text": "supported classes as indicated by the validity bits in the PLOGI LS_ACC Reply Sequence.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        634.96,
        495.52,
        646.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    }
  ],
  "asset_ids": []
}